summary:
The Security Council, 
Having considered the report of the Secretary-General on the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force, 
1. Calls upon the parties concerned to implement immediately its resolution 338 (1973); 
2. Welcomes efforts by the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force to implement the Secretary-Generalâ€™s zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse, requests the Secretary-General to continue taking necessary action and keep the Security Council informed, and urges troop-contributing countries to investigate and punish such acts; 
3. Decides to renew the mandate of the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force for six months, until 31 December 2009; 
4. Requests the Secretary-General to submit a report on developments and measures taken to implement resolution 338 (1973) at the end of this period.
